			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2340917">
									

<p>I like format screws when you're hiding information as easter eggs. I don't think the substantial majority of anything should be hidden &#8212; it's something else at that point.</p>
<p>And moreover, the vast majority of this tale would be completely inaccessible to anyone reading this on a mobile device. Which is another thing I really do not care for.</p>
<p>Oh, and is the source code intentionally obscured by all those pointless line breaks? Because it's annoying as shit and I can barely read it to begin with. Could you at least clean that up a bit, for the people who don't have the patience or sheer luck to stumble upon all of the levels of format screw in this?</p>
<p>As for the content&#8230; I'm <em>really</em> unsure about it. It's cool thoughts, but it feels&#8230; overpowered. It doesn't gel with what I feel are the most interesting ideas about the Foundation's relationship to reality and the rest of the world. Granted, there is good material on this site that does the same, but that material tends to get a pass by virtue of being a lot better than this.</p>
<p>EDIT: Just saw the picture. It's got a lot of image artifacts. I'm gonna fix that up for you and post it here.</p>
<p>EDIT2: <a href="http://i.imgur.com/YG8eUPi.png">Transparent version</a>, <a href="http://i.imgur.com/0CNJcIW.png">non-transparent version</a>. The transparent version should mesh better with whatever backgrounds or styles people might end up using on this page, but if that ends up fucking things up, just use the white-background one.</p>

