			<div class="content" id="post-content-2341053">
									

<p>Glad you like it! I'll work on the formatting stuff and the time thing.</p>
<p>Motherfuck! Antimemetics division?! I read all the orientations and looked through everything tagged memetics but couldn't find anything like this before I wrote it. Well…yeah maybe they just are rivals or don't know they exist. Are there any other tales/references to them? If for no other reason than I like reading stuff like this.</p>
<p>The gif has one frame of glitch as its last. I had 2 spread more out, but found them annoying to see when editing, as they distracted from the text. I didn't want it to make reading ad infinitum that much tougher,as this piece already asks a lot of effort from the reader.</p>
<p>The quotes I put around everything I wanted explicitly as Zack talking. People kept being put off by trying to wrap their heads around how people perceive stuff. The redacted technique is suppose to make people zone out unless they have clearance or natural ability. The white text drop down, black text, size zero and non-redacted hovers are meant to be info beneath the surface level of perception, and so no quotes. I left only one quote in around redacted as a sort of clue to draw attention. I'll think about it though.</p>

