					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrronin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1833724); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1833724&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203737" alt="MrRonin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1833724)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrronin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1833724); return false;" >MrRonin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1437435697 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Jul 2015 23:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2342012">
									

<p>I have to support Kalinin here (btw welcome back!). I didn't get it the first time, since I was reading on my tablet and didn't bother to gloss over anything. I read it the second time, and managed to discover all the hidden text. But even with all that extra stuff, it feels like extra fluff. To me this feels like the guy delivering the orientation is enjoying how much mindfuckery he can do to these poor recruits before saying &quot;surpr1s3!!! :D i have deceived you yet again.</p>
<p>The first one with the redacted was alright. The hidden collapsible had me confused. The footnote made sense, but then you lost me again with the size 0 text.</p>
<p>Maybe I just can't figure it out. But I'm not sure what this supposed to portray beyond putting memes within memes and hiring the select few who aren't phased by said memes.</p>

							</div>

								
					
