			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2342040">
									

<p>I don't know it this will help or make a difference, but here's what I was going for. The footnote explains all the deception is part of the training, because memetics override your thoughts, and you need to learn to be vigilant, even from sources you'd think you should be able to trust. The way its done is partly the orientation sarcastic tone, and the other part as misdirection. If you're focusing on what a dick Zack is, then you miss whatever that asshole is really doing.</p>
<p>The drop down was to indicate that the Division recruits ambitious probably worryingly amoral people, and they want to avoid another 2357 or worse. The last bit is a grandiose conception of what the Division thinks is happening in the world. It doesn't mean they're correct, its just their belief structure. The veil meaning keeping SCPs and all the other anomalies secret.</p>
<p>Sorry you found it confusing/didn't dig it.</p>

